com.esri.mo2.map.dpy
Interface Layerset

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable, GroupLayer, Layer
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseLayerset
public interface Layerset
extends GroupLayer

A LayerSet is a "top-level" GroupLayer. It is responsible for notifying interested LayerListeners of any changes in the organization of its Layers. The Layerset extends LayerListener in order to make available to GroupLayer constituents, a way to notify listeners - so, the LayerListener methods in Layerset provide the means for multicasting the event.

A Layerset "knows" about its corresponding DisplayManager so that constituent Layers can notify the DisplayManager when certain changes occur, such as when a Layer is changed from hidden to shown, or when the MapTip field changes.
